[0m[49m[39m  157, 165[0m:[39m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[39m  158, 166[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 159     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 160     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 161     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon SageMaker** | Trains and hosts registration models; runs preprocessing and fusion as Processing Jobs |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 162     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Stores DICOM files, preprocessed volumes, deformation fields, fused outputs |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 163     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS Step Functions** | Orchestrates the multi-step fusion pipeline with error handling and branching |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 164     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Tracks study metadata, registration quality metrics, processing status |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 165     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS Lambda** | Handles DICOM parsing, study matching, notification dispatch |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 166     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon HealthLake** | Provides DICOMweb-compliant medical image storage and retrieval |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 167     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon EC2 (GPU)** | Powers interactive clinical review and 3D visualization |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 168     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Manages encryption keys for all data stores |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 169     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon CloudWatch** | Monitors pipeline execution, latency, error rates, GPU utilization |
